In celebration of this month's 87th annual Academy Awards, a fashion-loving pastry chef from New York City has created intricate cookie replicas of famous actresses and their iconic Oscar gowns.

Jansen Chan, a director of pastry operations at the International Culinary Center, used sugar paste and cookie dough to duplicate the dresses worn by Angelina Jolie, Reese Witherspoon, Halle Berry, Nicole Kidman, Lupita Nyong'o, Michelle Williams and Penelope Cruz.

The confectionery designs were made in the shape of the stars' specific red carpet poses and included their signature hairstyles and jewelry - with each cookie taking Mr Chan eight hours to make.

