But Mr Chan isn't the only person making edible designs to pay tribute to pop-culture. 

Last December, Martha Stewart created a gingerbread replica of the mansion from Downton Abbey.

And in April 2014, British artist Nathan Wyburn used various crackers from UK food giant Jacobs to make stencil artworks of fashion icons, including Kate Moss, Cara Delevingne and Harry Styles.  

